<HEADLINE> Arab Lawyers to Campaign for Palestinians' Rights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 25 (Xinhua) -- The Arab Lawyers Union will
launch a wide-scale campaign to confront Israeli plots on
Jerusalem and rally support the Palestinian people, the union
chief said on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The union is scheduled to organize meeting at its headquarters
in Cairo on Monday to discuss the details of the planned campaign,
Farouk Abu Issa said in remarks carried by Egypt's Middle East
News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will be attended by representatives of Arab,
regional and international organizations, Palestinian and Arab
intellectuals, and international law experts, Abu Issa said.
</P>
<P>
The objective of the meeting is to reiterate the legitimacy of
the United Nations resolutions on Middle East issues, especially
those related to Jerusalem, he added.
</P>
<P>
The participants will discuss ways of protecting the holy city
against judaization by Israel and maintaining its Islamic
characteristics, the Arab union secretary general said.
</P>
<P>
They will seek to uphold Arab right to the traditional Arab
East Jerusalem and promote the Palestinians' legitimate struggle
to establish an independent state with East Jerusalem as the
capital, Abu Issa said.
</P>
<P>
U.N. resolutions stipulate that Jerusalem is under the control
of the world organization. But Israel captured the whole of the
city in wars with Arabs and declared in 1980 that Jerusalem was
its "eternal and undivided capital."
</P>
<P>
The Palestinians want East Jerusalem as capital of their future
independent state.
</P>
<P>
The two sides have begun negotiations for a final peace
agreement on the thorny issues including Jerusalem and the
Palestinian statehood. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
