<HEADLINE> Two Killed in U.S. Plane Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Two people, including the
pilot and passenger, were killed as a small plane crashed Saturday
in Nashville of Tennessee State, the United States, reports
reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
The reports quoted Fire Chief Buck Dozier as saying that it was
miraculous that no one on the ground was killed when the private
plane crashed on a busy neighborhood street at around 11 a.m.
local time.
</P>
<P>
"This is a heavily populated area and an historic area of
Nashville. It came down between two houses and just burst into
flames," Dozier said.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the crash was unknown. 
</P>
</TEXT>
