<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2000 GMT, Saturday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN -- An earthquake measuring 5.1 degrees on Richter scale
hit Iran's southern coastal province of Bushehr Friday night,
causing slight damage to a number of rural houses.
</P>
<P>
The seismography base of Shiraz, affiliated to the Geophysics
Institute of Tehran University, registered the epicenter of the
tremor 160 kilometers southwest of Shiraz, capital city of
Bushehr's neighboring Fars province.
</P>
<P>
The tremor hit the area at 10:47 p.m. local time (1917 GMT)
Friday night. (BC-Iran-Quake)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
AMMAN -- The chief lawyer of 21 detained members of the
militant Palestinian Islamic Resistance Movement (Hamas) in Jordan
is seeking the release on bail of two of the Hamas leaders.
</P>
<P>
Saleh Armouti, who heads a 60-man team defending the 21 Hamas
members arrested during a government crackdown on the radical
group, said he is seeking to bail out Hamas politburo chief Khalid
Mishaal and spokesman Ibrahim Ghosheh. (BC-Jordan-Hamas)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- The Arab League on Saturday warned that the Middle
East peace process would collapse unless Jerusalem restores its
status and its islamic feature.
</P>
<P>
The league issued the warning in a statement released by its
general secretariat one day ahead of the Jerusalem Day.
</P>
<P>
The Arab nation has opted for peace as a strategic goal, said
the 22-nation pan-Arab forum. But the cherished objective will not
be realized until an independent Palestinian state is established
with Jerusalem as its capital, the league said.
(BC-Arab League-Israel-Jerusalem)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Iraq on Saturday declared its readiness to
cooperate with international oil companies including
U.S. companies to supply Iraq's oil sector with the required oil
equipment and spare parts.
</P>
<P>
Oil Undersecretary Taha Hammoud Mousa made the remarks at an
inauguration ceremony for an oil and gas technology exhibition
currently held in Baghdad with the participation of 56 Arab and
foreign oil companies. (BC-Iraq-US-Oil)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- The Arab Lawyers Union will launch a wide-scale
campaign to confront Israeli plots on Jerusalem and rally support
the Palestinian people, the union chief said on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The union is scheduled to organize meeting at its headquarters
in Cairo on Monday to discuss the details of the planned campaign,
Farouk Abu Issa said in remarks carried by Egypt's Middle East
News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will be attended by representatives of Arab,
regional and international organizations, Palestinian and Arab
