<HEADLINE> Saudi Crown Prince Meets Tunisian Defense Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Crown Prince and
Deputy Prime Minister Abdullah Ibn Abdul-Aziz met in Riyadh on
Saturday with visiting Tunisian Defense Minister Al-Habib Bin
Yahya for talks on bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Bin Yahya delivered a letter from Tunisian
President Zine El Abidine Ben Ali to Saudi King Fahd Ibn
Abdul-Aziz, according to the Saudi Press Agency monitored here.
But it did not disclose the contents of the message.
</P>
<P>
The Tunisian defense minister, who arrived in Saudi Arabia on
Friday, had earlier said that his visit to the Gulf kingdom came
within the framework of continuing consultations between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
The visit, he said, also reflected the keenness of the
leadership of the two Arab sates on strengthening bilateral
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Bin Yahya, earlier in the day, visited the public institution
for military industries in the Kharj region in southern Saudi
Arabia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
