<HEADLINE> Sino-Kenyan Relations Very Strong: Kenyan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan President Daniel arap
Moi said Saturday that the relations between China and Kenya are
very strong.
</P>
<P>
The president made the remarks at a Chinese donation presenting
ceremony at a high school in Nakuru, the capital of Kenya's
Central Province.
</P>
<P>
China's NeoKing Take Limited donated the Nakuru Moi High school
20 computers worth more than 20,000 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Computers are very important for Kenya's technology
development, President Moi said, adding that the Chinese donation
demonstrates the spirit of cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The students and teachers at the school appreciated the
computers very much.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador in Kenya An Yongyu was also present at the
ceremony. 
</P>
</TEXT>
