<HEADLINE> OPEC Ministers To Convene in Venezuela </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, December 25 (Xinhua) -- The next Organization of
Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC) Ordinary Conference of
Ministers will be held in Caracas, Venezuela, on March 27, 2000.
</P>
<P>
The announcement was made by the OPEC Information and Public
Relations Department in an official communique from the Venezuelan
Mines and Energy Ministry (MEM) released Saturday here.
</P>
<P>
The Conference of Ministers to be held in Venezuela is the
result of a long diplomatic campaign among the OPEC members
promoted by MEM directors Ali Rodriguez and Alvaro Silva Calderon.
</P>
<P>
The Second Summit of the OPEC member countries, a project
proposed by Venezuelan President Hugo Chavez, will be held in the
Venezuelan capital, according to the communique. Alvaro Silva and
Foreign Vice Minister Jorge Valero made an extensive tour recently
of the OPEC member countries and obtained support from most of the
member countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
