<HEADLINE> Middle East Economic Briefs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 25 (Xinhua) -- The following are economic
briefs from the Middle East countries.
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- The Japanese government has agreed to grant Egypt
loans to finance a project on developing wind power stations in
the Eastern-desert Xa'frana area, the Arabic daily al-Alam al-Youm
reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese government also planned to extend another package
to help Egypt build a solar energy station in the southern Toshka
zone and a nearby 10,000-kilowatt solar energy plant currently under
construction at an investment of 500,000 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
DUBAI -- Dubai will host an Arab International Fair of Oil,
Gas, Marine and Land-based Petrochemical Industries serving the
Gulf states with the participation of 200 companies from 20
countries.
</P>
<P>
The fair is the biggest of its kind in the Arab world where
up-to-date oil and gas industry-related equipment is to be
displayed, the Arabic daily al-Alam al-Youm reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
International groups from Belgium, Britain, China, France,
Germany and firms from North America, Western Europe, the
Commonwealth of Independent States, Southeastern Asia and the GCC
countries would take part in the event, said the report.
</P>
<P>
AMMAN -- The U.S Overseas Private Investment Corporation
will extend a package of 55 million U.S. dollars to Jordan's
Aqaba Railway Company, the Arabic daily al-Alam al-Youm reported
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The money will be used to help the Jordanian government carry
out the company's privatization program and build new lines.
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- The Egyptian International Exhibition and Fair
Authority is to organize an international fair of packaging and
wrapping equipment from November 23 to 28.
</P>
<P>
The total world expenditure on packaging and wrapping equipment
hit nearly 750 billion U.S dollars per year, about 1.5 to 7
percent of the total gross domestic product (GDP) in most
countries, the al-Alam al-Youm daily quoted Egyptian Trade and
Supply Minister Ahmed Gowaili as saying.
</P>
<P>
In Egypt, the annual spending in this industry is over one
billion dollars, said the minister.
</P>
<P>
The Arab world consumption of packaging and wrapping material
reached about 5.5 million tons, while its total production is only
3.3 million tons, meeting 64 percent of the demands. 
</P>
</TEXT>
