<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 25 (Xinhua) -- The fourth phase of polling
for the 13th Lok Sabha elections Saturday recorded a turnout of
over 51 percent, the Election Commission said.
</P>
<P>
However, five people were killed and more than 20 people
injured Saturday in poll-related violence.
</P>
