<HEADLINE> Over 65 Tons of Drugs Seized in Peru </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Peruvian police have seized more
than 65 tons of drugs this year in different actions in the
country and dismembered 40 drug trafficking organizations.
</P>
<P>
The National Antidrug Direction (Dinandro) announced Saturday
that police confiscated 6,273 kilos of cocaine basic paste, 3,106
kilos of cocaine hydrochloride, 6,482 kilos of marihuana, 38.6
kilos of opium poppy gum, 664 grams of heroin hydrochloride,
44,029 kilograms of opium poppy, and 193 kilos of opium poppy
seeds, among other drugs.
</P>
<P>
It also seized more than 100 tons of chemical inputs, like
sulphuric acid, acetone, sodium carbonate, potasium permanganate,
hydrochloric acid, calcium oxyde, kerosene and other substances.
</P>
<P>
Dinandro personnel secured 40 real state pieces, 114 vehicles,
three aircraft, eight boats, 19 revolvers, 32 automatic pistols,
30 shotguns, and 14 rifles. The ordnance was used by the mafias to
protect their cultivation areas.
</P>
<P>
Police detained at the Lima international airport 50 carriers,
most of them foreigners, and seized more than 150 kilos of cocaine
hydrochloride that was about to be taken to Chile, the
Netherlands, Spain, Brazil, the United States and Argentina.
</P>
</TEXT>
