<HEADLINE> Belarus to Introduce Draft Resolution Barring New Mass </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Belarus said Saturday
that it would introduce a draft resolution at the 54th session of
the United Nations General Assembly aimed at barring development
and manufacture of new weapons of mass destruction.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the general debate of the current session of the
General Assembly, Ural Latypov, minister of foreign affairs of
Belarus, said his country made an historical decision a few years
ago when it relinquished possession of nuclear arms inherited from
the former Soviet Union.
</P>
<P>
"The nuclear powers are still not ready to fully relinquish the
possession of such arms. There is pressing need to withdraw them
from as much of the world as possible, especially from heavily
populated regions," the minister said.
</P>
<P>
He urged Central and Eastern Europe to agree to binding legal
commitments not to deploy nuclear weapons on their territory,
saying this would be of paramount importance to the European
family of nations. 
</P>
