<DOCNO> XIE19990926.0031 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Publishes Popular Defense Science Series </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 26 (Xinhua)-- China today published a series
of books on national defense science, in a bid to propagate
defense science and improve people's defense awareness.
</P>
<P>
The series, the most authoritative of its kind in China, was
compiled by the Commission of Science, Technology and Industry for
National Defense, a body in charge of the nation's defense
industry and scientific research.
</P>
<P>
The five volumes of the series cover nuclear energy, aviation,
space, warships, and weaponry. These books systematically
introduce the evolution of the defense industry, and
comprehensively provide scientific and technical knowledge about
such defense topics as electronic information and new weapons.
</P>
<P>
The series is mainly designed for readers above the junior high
school level, while some parts are a bit advanced in order to "
leave some thinking room for those who want to acquire a deeper
understanding of defense science," sources say.
</P>
<P>
In order to ensure the authority of the series, the commission
invited technical consultants to help compile and edit the work,
including several academicians with the Chinese Academy of Science
and senior specialists with long experience in defense technology.
</P>
</TEXT>
