<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Highlights of Today's Diplomatic News </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Following are the highlights
of the diplomatic news released by Xinhua today.
</P>
<P>
 NPC Vice-Chairperson Meets Japanese Visitors
</P>
<P>
BEIJING, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Peng Peiyun, vice-chairperson
of the Chinese National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee,
met with a delegation from the Women's Committee of Japan-China
Friendship Association led by committee chairman Nagaike Hiroko
here this evening.
</P>
<P>
The delegation is here on a visit at the invitation of the All-
China Women's Federation with peng as its president.
</P>
<P>
Senior Singaporean Minister Visits Suzhou
</P>
<P>
SUZHOU, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Singaporean Senior Minister
Lee Kuan Yew visited Suzhou in east China's Jiangsu Province
yesterday and today.
</P>
<P>
Chen Huanyou, secretary of the Jiangsu Provincial Committee of
the Communist Party of China (CPC), during a meeting with Lee here
on Saturday evening, pointed to the great contributions made by
Lee in Sino-Singapore joint development of the Suzhou Industrial
Park.
</P>
<P>
The development of the park over the past five years shows that
learning from Singapore's experience has proved to be a success
in Suzhou, Chen said, adding that he hopes bilateral cooperation
will be further expanded.
</P>
<P>
Lee, who is on his sixth visit to Suzhou, voiced satisfaction
with the progress of the park and said he will continue to support
the park's development.
</P>
<P>
This morning, Lee and Chen also attended the opening ceremony
of the Central Park in the Suzhou Industrial Park. 
</P>
