<HEADLINE> South African champion sets new short course breaststroke record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DURBAN, September 26, (Xinhua) -- Penny Heyns of South Africa
broke her own world short-course record in the 100-meter
breaststroke Sunday, finishing in 1:05.40 at the Seagulls short-
course championships.
</P>
<P>
The double Olympic champion shaved 0.17 seconds off the record
she set earlier this month at the South African championships.
</P>
<P>
It was her thirteenth world record. Since late July, she has
broken eight long course marks in the 50, 100 and 200. The short
course is swum in a 25-meter pool. 
</P>
