<HEADLINE> Iranian Province Hit by Quake for Second Successive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Another 4.8-magnitude
earthquake hit Bushehr province in southern Iran for the second
successive night at 22:49 local time (19:19 gmt) on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The seismography base of Shiraz, affiliated to the Geophysics
Institute of Tehran University , registered the epicenter of the
earthquake 160 kilometers southwest of Shiraz, capital city of
Fars Province.
</P>
<P>
Casualties resulting from the earthquake are not immediately
known.
</P>
<P>
An earthquake measuring 5.1 degrees on the Richter scale rocked
the province Friday night, causing damage to a number of rural
houses.
</P>
<P>
Fourteen people were injured in the provincial city of
Tangestan as a result of the Friday quake. 
