<HEADLINE> China to Strengthen Party Leadership in SOEs (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Strengthening and improving
the Party leadership is the fundamental guarantee for speeding up
the reform and development of state-owned enterprises (SOEs) in
China, according to a Party document issued today.
</P>
<P>
The Decision of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of
China (CPC) on Major Issues Concerning the Reform and Development
of State-Owned Enterprises stresses that it is a major principle
to adhere to the Party leadership and bring into play the role of
Party organizations in SOEs as the political core, and SOEs should
have no wavering over the principle at any time.
</P>
<P>
The Decision points out that to lift SOEs out of difficulties,
efforts must be made to establish a leading system as well as an
organizational and managerial system in SOEs that conform to the
law of the market economy and China's actual situation. Efforts
are also needed to improve the SOE leadership, give play to the
role of Party organizations in SOEs as the political core, and
adhere to the principle of relying on the working class whole-
heartedly.
</P>
<P>
The effort to pay attention to the Party's political advantages
should be combined that to make use of market mechanisms so as to
mobilize every positive factor to pool efforts for the smooth
implementation of reform and development in SOEs.
</P>
<P>
The role of the SOE Party organizations as the political core
is mainly reflected in ensuring and supervising the implementation
of the Party and state policies in related enterprises;
participating in making decisions on major issues, supporting the
board of share-holders, board of directors, board of supervisors
and managers or directors in exercising their functions and powers
according to law; and whole-heartedly relying on staff and workers,
and leading and supporting trade unions and non-government
organizations including the Communist Youth League, as well as the
workers' congress, to function independently according to law and
their respective regulations.
</P>
<P>
Their role is also seen in guiding enterprises' ideological and
political education as well as ethical and cultural progress in an
effort to forge ranks of workers and staff members that have lofty
ideals, moral integrity, a good education and a strong sense of
discipline; and in strengthening the building of the Party
organizations themselves, improving education on the Party spirit
and work style, and giving full play to the roles of the Party
branches as a fighting bastion and the Party members as an
exemplary vanguard, it says.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
