<HEADLINE> CPPCC Meeting On State Enterprises Reform Closes (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 26 (Xinhua) -- The 9th Standing Committee of
the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC) ended its seventh session here
today, emphasizing the reform of China's state enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of the National Committee of the CPPCC Li Ruihuan and
other senior officials attended the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Chen Jinhua, vice-chairman of the CPPCC National Committee,
said that the meeting held discussions on the Decision on Issues
Related to State-Owned Enterprise Reforms and Development, which
was issued by the 4th plenum of the 15th Communist Party of China
(CPC) Central Committee on September 22.
</P>
<P>
Chen said that in order to implement the spirit of the plenum
of the CPC Central Committee, the session's participants earnestly
studied the decision, which contains guidelines for the reform and
growth of state enterprises.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the decision has the following four
characteristics: it defines the range of reform of state-owned
economy structure; it brings forward a request to set up a modern
enterprise system to meet the demands of socialized production and
a market economy; it approves favorable policies and measures for
the development of state-owned enterprises; it stresses that
problems in the economic structure have become the major influence
on social and economic development.
</P>
<P>
Chen pointed out that establishing a modern enterprise system
is a necessary requirement for developing socialized mass
production and a market economy, and also an effective way to
combine public ownership and a market economy.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
