<HEADLINE> Largest Taiwan-funded Auto Joint Venture in Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, September 26 (Xinhua)-- The first phase of an auto-
production project, the largest auto joint venture funded by the
Chinese mainland and Taiwan, went into operation today in Fuzhou,
capital of Fujian Province in east China.
</P>
<P>
Jointly funded by the Fuzhou Automotive Works of the Fujian
Auto Group and a major Taiwan auto giant, Dongnan Auto City was
built with 230 million U.S. dollars for the first phase of
construction, with an annual production capacity of 60,000 sedans.
</P>
<P>
Corporate sources say the auto works can produce 300,000 motor
vehicles a year when the entire three-phase construction is
completed. By that time, Dongnan Auto City is expected to become
one of China's major automobile producers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
