<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Maps Out Objectives, Guiding Principles for SOE Reform and Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 26 (Xinhua) -- China has defined major
objectives and guiding principles for the reform and development
of State-owned enterprises (SOEs) in a decision of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC), which was issued
here today.
</P>
<P>
The Decision of the CPC Central Committee on Major Issues
Concerning the Reform and Development of State-owned Enterprises
was adopted at the 4th Plenum of the 15th CPC Central Committee on
September 22.
</P>
<P>
The objectives for SOEs' reform and development up to the year
2010 are basically completing strategic readjustment and
restructuring, bringing into form a more rational layout and
structure of the national economy, establishing a relatively
perfect modern corporate system, markedly improving economic
performance, remarkably promoting scientific and technological
development, market competition and risk-resisting, and making the
state economy play a better, dominant role in the national economy.
</P>
<P>
The guidelines for the reform and development of the SOEs
include: maintaining public ownership as the dominant form;
strategically readjusting the layout of the state economy and
restructuring the SOEs; establishing a modern corporate system;
and fostering a competitive mechanism of survival of the fittest.
</P>
</TEXT>
