<HEADLINE> Park Depicting the USA Opens In E. China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, September 26 (Xinhua) -- The first park created in
China to present the customs, history and culture of the United
States opened to visitors today in Hangzhou, capital of east China
's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
The park covers more than 13.3 hectares and was built at a cost
of 180 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
In the park, visitors will find examples of some renowned
American architecture, including a White House which is the same
size as the real building, and churches and villages, along with a
chance to tour the attractive scenery of Hawaii.
</P>
<P>
The park is expected to be an added attraction for the scenic
city of Hangzhou, a popular tourist destination renowned for the
beauty of its West Lake. 
</P>
</TEXT>
