<HEADLINE> Get-Together Of People From Friendship Cities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, September 26 (Xinhua) -- A get-together of people
from many of Hangzhou's friendship cities was held today in this
capital city of east China's Zhejiang Province, attended by 1,228
people from 18 countries which have friendship ties with Hangzhou,
one of China's most famous tourist destinations.
</P>
<P>
The three-day activity, the second of its kind ever held in the
province, is expected to further promote economic, cultural,
educational, and scientific and technological exchange and
cooperation between the friendship cities.
</P>
<P>
Since 1979, Hangzhou has established friendship relationships
with 43 cities in 23 countries.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of friendship ties has helped promote
economic growth in the city, making it possible for the creation
of 136 overseas-funded enterprises, the use of 530 million U.S.
dollars of overseas investment, and the holding of a number of
trade and investment fairs locally. 
