<HEADLINE> Big Party in Macao Celebrates New China's 50th Birthday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Attended by more than 1,000
people from all walks of life, a grand gathering was held here
Sunday morning to mark the 50th anniversary of the founding of the
People's Republic of China (PRC).
</P>
<P>
Ma Man Kei, presidium chairman of a local preparatory committee
for celebrating the anniversary, expressed the common wish of the
Macao people that the motherland will grow stronger and more
prosperous.
</P>
<P>
"Under the leadership of the Communist Party of China and
through the concerted hard work of the people all over the country,
China has shown earth-shaking changes since our New China was
founded 50 years ago," said the 80-year-old Ma, who is also
chairman of the Macao Chamber of Commerce.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the country enjoys unprecedented economic
strength, its productivity is greatly boosted and the people have
much higher living standards. "History is a good testimony that
the Socialist system has incomparable advantage and vitality and
that the Chinese people have a strong cohesive force."
</P>
<P>
While celebrating the 50th birthday of the PRC, Macao residents
are happy to see Macao's return to the motherland, Ma said. After
Hong Kong, Macao's return will be another good example to
demonstrate the correctness of the "one country, two systems"
concept.
</P>
<P>
"The fate of Macao has been closely linked with that of the
motherland. We are fully aware of the fact that only a stronger
motherland can give Macao a promising future," Ma said.
</P>
<P>
He called on Macao residents of various social quarters to take
an active part in the preparatory work for the establishment of
the Macao Special Administrative Region on December 20 and build a
better future.
</P>
<P>
Edmund Ho Hau Wah, chief executive-designate of the Macao SAR,
and Wang Qiren, director of the Xinhua News Agency Macao Branch,
joined local residents at the party, where artistic performances
were also staged.
</P>
<P>
Over the past days, social bodies in Macao have been holding
various gatherings to celebrate the 50th anniversary of the
founding of the PRC. 
</P>
