<HEADLINE> Prisoners Take Prison Guards Hostage in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Political Prisoners took as
hostages dozens of prison guards in various jails in Turkey on
sunday, the semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported here.
</P>
<P>
The political prisoners were reacting to an incident in which
seven prisoners were killed in the uprising in the Anakra Main
Covered Jail early Sunday morning, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
The prisoners took hostage seven prison guards at the Bartin
Special Type Covered Prison on Sunday. Eyewitnesses said they
heard gunfire from within the prison in Bartin province.
</P>
<P>
Security measures have tightened in and around the prison.
</P>
<P>
The agency added that at the Bayrampasa and Umraniye prisons in
Istanbul, the largest city of Turkey, prisoners who were
sentenced with terrorist crimes took hostage a total of 18 prison
guards.
</P>
<P>
Reinforcement units have been deployed at the both
prisons in Istanbul.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, prisoners took hostage nine prison guards at the
Canakkale E-Type Covered Prison and 10 prison guards at the
Cankiri E-Type Covered Prison.
</P>
<P>
Early Sunday morning, seven people were killed and seven
others injured in clashes between the Turkish security forces
and prisoners at Ankara Main Covered Jail as the forces tried
to enter into the wards in a bid to transfer the inmates
to prisons in other provinces.
</P>
<P>
The prisoners set up barricades and used pistols or bottles
to stop the security forces from carrying out their mission.
</P>
