<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Members of the public here
in Hong Kong have been advised to stay at home for their own
safety as Storm Signal No. 8 was hoisted at 05:20 a.m. Sunday.
</P>
<P>
A government spokesman urged members of the public to stay
where they are and not to go outside unless absolutely necessary,
as gale force winds will affect Hong Kong when tropical storm Cam
is edging closer to Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
At 06:00 a.m. tropical storm Cam was centered about 80
kilometers southeast of Hong Kong and is forecast to move
northwest at about 10 kilometers per hour toward Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The Home Affairs Department has opened 28 temporary shelters
and so far 28 people have sought refuge at these shelters.
</P>
<P>
Ferry services in inner harbor routes and outlying routes have
been suspended until further notice.
</P>
<P>
Tram and peak tram services have also been suspended.
</P>
<P>
Kowloon-Canton Railway Corporation (KCRC) services, airport
express line and Tung Chung line are all operating at 10-minute
intervals. 
