<HEADLINE> Nigerian Passports Traded in Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Nigerian passports are being
traded in western Europe by some Nigerians, a leading Nigerian
newspaper reported on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Guardian quoted the Foreign Affairs Ministry sources as
saying Nigerian embassies had presented the seized passports to
the minister of state for foreign affairs Dubun Onyia.
</P>
<P>
It was learnt that a memo is underway from the Foreign Affairs
Ministry to the Internal Affairs Ministry on the worrying
development and an overhaul of the immigration department is
requested.
</P>
<P>
The passport trade was believed to be connected with the high
price of the document overseas. Renewal of passport in Germany
costs 200 U.S. dollars, in the United States 60 dollars and in
Britain 20 pounds.
</P>
<P>
An official at the Nigerian embassy in Germany told Onyia that
the high cost of passport acquisition and renewal is traceable to
the directive of government that embassies should generate
revenue.
</P>
<P>
It was learnt that those who patronize the illegal market
include Nigerians who travelled overseas with the passports of
other west African countries.  
</P>
