<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990926.0064 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's SOEs Urged to Trim Off Payrolls (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 26 (Xinhua) -- The Decision of the Communist
Party of China Central Committee on Major Issues Concerning the
Reform and Development of State-Owned Enterprises (SOEs), which
was published today, urges SOEs to do a good job in reducing
workforce, improving efficiency, re-employing displaced workers,
and guaranteeing social security.
</P>
<P>
Laying off redundant workers to increase enterprise efficiency
and helping these displaced workers to get re-employed is an
important part of the SOE reform, the Decision says.
</P>
<P>
Streamlining the workforce should be well combined with
increasing efficiency so as to attain the goal of reducing cost,
increase efficiency and profitability in the enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Qualified SOEs should create economic entities that are
financially independent and responsible for their own economic
losses and profits by separating their main business from other
business operations and diverting part of the workers to some
auxiliary posts, so that some redundant workers could get re-
employed and the pressure on social employment could be alleviated.
</P>
<P>
Procedures of laying off workers should be standardized, re-
employment centers should be set up inside the enterprises, and
laid-off workers need to be granted basic living to maintain
social stability.
</P>
<P>
The work of laying off workers should be adapted to the State
fiscal strength and capability of the society to absorb the
unemployed, it says.
</P>
<P>
Great efforts should be put into the task of re-employment of
laid-off workers. Effective policies and measures should be
adopted to increase job opportunities. The service sector should
be boosted to absorb more laid-off workers, who also need guidance
to change their stereotyped opinion in job selection. Efforts are
also needed for training the laid-off workers so as to increase
the chances for them to land new jobs.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990926.0065 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's SOEs Urged to Trim Off Payrolls (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Preferential policies should be improved to facilitate the re-
employment of displaced workers, encouraging them to get re-
employed as soon as possible by accepting jobs in non-public
economic entities, starting their own business or becoming self-
employed.
</P>
<P>
As for those who start business of their own, the government
should grant them more support in getting official permits,
finding office sites, enjoying tax reduction or exemption, and
receiving bank loans. The labor market should be actively
developed and regulated so a market-oriented employment mechanism
could be formed, the Decision stresses.
</P>
<P>
It points out that speeding up the building of the social
security system is an important prerequisite for a smooth
implementation of the SOE reform. The social security services
such as endowment, unemployment and medical insurance should cover
people of a wider range, and SOEs, collectively-owned enterprises,
overseas-funded ventures and private businesses and their
employees should all take part in the social security program, and
hand in insurance premium.
</P>
<P>
Efforts should be increased to collect the insurance premium,
increase its rate, pursue enterprises' arrears of the premium so
as to ensure that the pension can be paid on time and in full
amount.
</P>
<P>
A unified management plan of retirement pension funds at the
provincial-level should be further improved, and multiple measures
such as selling off some State assets and adjusting the fiscal
spending structure should be taken to establish new fund-raising
channels for the social security program and replenish the social
funds.
</P>
<P>
Social insurance funds should be strictly managed, supervision
should be strengthened on such management and no funds should be
used for other purposes than insurance payments to ensure the
safety and increment in value of the funds.
</P>
<P>
Provision of social insurance should be gradually socialized.
Retirees should disengage from the enterprises, receive retirement
pensions at social service agencies and be managed by communities
instead of enterprises.
</P>
<P>
It is imperative to ensure the political and welfare of retired
veteran cadres and provide them with good services.  
</P>
</TEXT>
