<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Speed Up SOE Technical Upgrading </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 26 (Xinhua) -- to achieve sustained, fast
and healthy economic development, attention should be paid to keep
up with the global trend in adjustment of industrial structure and
changing demand of domestic and overseas markets, and speeding up
the technological renovation and industrial upgrading, according
to the a decision of the Communist Part of China Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
The Decision of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of
China on Major Issues Concerning the Reform and Development of
State-Owned Enterprises (SOEs) was published today.
</P>
<P>
The Decision says that the direction and emphasis of SOEs in
technological renovation and industrial upgrading should be
employing advanced technology to transform the traditional
industries and strengthening technological renovation of existent
enterprises with the market as the guide and with the goal of
increasing product diversity, improving quality, improving
efficiency and spurring exports.
</P>
<P>
The direction and emphasis also include holding an important
position in new and hi-tech industries in electronic information,
bio-engineering, new energy, new materials, aviation, space
technology and environmental protection, and mastering core
technologies so as to serve as an industrial leader.
</P>
<P>
With technological renovation and industrial upgrading, a few
large enterprises and enterprise groups should reach or near the
advanced world level in terms of product quality, manufacturing
technology and equipment, and labor productivity, and establish
themselves in the world market.
</P>
<P>
Most enterprises should actively participate in market
competition at home and abroad by pushing ahead with technology
renovation and industrial upgrading and making full use of the
advantage of the nation's sufficient labor resources, it says.
</P>
<P>
Active and effective policies, including increased input,
subsidized bank loans, tax incentives, industrial investment funds
and venture capital funds, should be adopted to support the
technological renovation and industrial upgrading of the
enterprises, and funds should also be pooled from domestic and
overseas capital markets. In addition, policy incentives should be
offered to facilitate the commercial use of research achievements.
</P>
<P>
The Decision points out that enterprises should be taken as
principal participants in technological renovation and it is
imperative to establish a technological renovation system with
enterprises as its central consideration. Large enterprises should
set up technological development centers, develop core products
with their own intellectual patents.
</P>
<P>
Industrial production, research and development of technologies
should be combined, technological personnel in scientific research
institutions and institutions of higher learning should be
encouraged to join enterprises or enterprise groups, development
and spreading of practical technologies should be intensified, and
input into experimental application of new technologies should be
increased, so as to facilitate the translation of technological
developments into real productive forces.  
</P>
</TEXT>
