<DOCNO> XIE19990926.0073 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Readjust Layout of State Economy (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 26 (Xinhua) -- China will take strategic
steps to readjust its over-distributed and poor-performing state
economy, according to a decision adopted by the 4th Plenum of the
15th Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC).
</P>
<P>
The Decision of the CPC Central Committee on Major Issues
Concerning the Reform and Development of State-owned Enterprises,
which was made public here today, details the guiding principles
for readjusting the layout of the state economy.
</P>
<P>
The Decision points out that under a socialist market economy,
the leading role of the state economy in the national economy
hinges upon its power to control. The role of the state economy
should be materialized through solely state-owned enterprises as
well as through making greater efforts to develop a shareholding
system.
</P>
<P>
State economy should command a dominant stake in key industries
and crucial fields deemed as the lifeline of the national economy,
in order to shore up, guide and push ahead overall social and
economic development and play a key role in achieving State-set
macro-economic control targets.
</P>
<P>
State economy should be maintained at a necessary size, with
its layout further optimized and the quality further improved, the
Decision notes.
</P>
<P>
In different stages of economic development, the document says,
the proportion of the state economy in different industries and
areas may vary, but its layout should be adjusted.
</P>
<P>
It says that the strategic readjustment of the layout of the
national economy should be combined with the optimization and
upgrading of industrial structure and the readjustment and
improvement of the structure of ownership.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990926.0074 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Readjust Layout of State Economy (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Industries and fields that need to be controlled by the state
economy include: industries that are related to state security,
industries that are monopolized by their nature, industries that
supply public-use products and services, and backbone enterprises
in pillar industries and new and high technology industries, the
document points out.
</P>
<P>
In other industries and fields, it says, the entire quality of
the state economy could be improved through assets regrouping and
structural adjustment to centralize their capacity and strengthen
the key state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Along with the sustained growth of the national economy, the
development of the state economy has a vast space, with its
aggregate power expected to be further increased, overall quality
further improved, and layout more rational, though the proportion
it holds in the entire national economy might decrease. The
decline, however, will not affect the socialist nature of the
country, so long as China upholds public ownership as the main
form, the State controls the lifeline of the national economy, and
the controlling power and competitiveness of the state economy are
strengthened, the Decision says.
</P>
<P>
Effective policies and measures will be adopted to accelerate
the readjustment of the state economy in old industrial bases and
the central and western parts of the country, the Decision says.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
