<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 1 Killed, 27 Injured in Bus Blast in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 26 (Xinhua) -- At least one passenger were
killed and 27 others were injured Sunday afternoon in eastern Sri
Lanka when the bus they were traveling in was hit by a bomb blast,
informed sources said.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the blast happened around 1:00 p.m. local time
at Passara, about 200 kilometers east of Colombo.
</P>
<P>
The injured has been rushed to local hospitals.
</P>
<P>
No one has yet claimed responsibility for the blast. But the
sources believed that it was the work of separatist Liberation
Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE).
</P>
<P>
In recent weeks, the LTTE rebels have stepped up attacks in the
east after heavy fighting was reported in the northern Wanni
region as the government troops made another attempt to capture
more territory.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month, 54 Sinhalese civilians were hacked to death
by LTTE rebels in attacks on three villages in the eastern Amparai
district.
</P>
<P>
On Friday LTTE rebels ambushed a military convoy in the eastern
Batticaloa town, killing 18 soldiers on a bus with remote
controlled claymore mine.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE have been fighting a 16-year-old war against the
government for a separate homeland for minority Tamils in Sri
Lanka's north and east. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
