<DOCNO> XIE19990926.0077 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Sets Trans-Century Blueprint for SOE Reform and Development ( 2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The major objectives for SOEs' reform and development by the
year of 2010 are basically completing strategic readjustment and
restructuring, bringing into form a more rational lay-out and
structure of the national economy, establishing a relatively
perfect modern corporate system, markedly improving economic
performance, markedly strengthening scientific and technological
development, market competition and risk-resisting, and giving the
state sector a better dominant role in the national economy in
accordance with the fundamental transformation of the economic
structure and economic growth mode, and with the needs of opening
up further to the outside world.
</P>
<P>
The Decision sets out the following guiding principles in
promoting SOEs' reform and development:
</P>
<P>
-- With public ownership as the dominant form, diverse forms of
ownership develop side by side.
</P>
<P>
-- Strategically readjusting the lay-out of the state sector
and restructuring the SOEs.
</P>
<P>
-- Combining reforms with restructuring, regrouping, and
enhancement of management.
</P>
<P>
-- Establishing the modern corporate system.
</P>
<P>
-- Pushing forward scientific and technological advancement of
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
-- Comprehensively enhancing enterprise management.
</P>
<P>
-- Establishing competitive mechanism of survival of the
fittest.
</P>
<P>
-- Coordinating the carrying-out of various supplementary
reforms.
</P>
<P>
-- Whole-heartedly relying on the working class and exploiting
the core role of the Party organizations within enterprises.
</P>
<P>
-- Promoting enterprises' ethical and cultural progress.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
