<DOCNO> XIE19990926.0079 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Sets Trans-Century Blueprint for SOE Reform and Development ( 3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The strategic readjustment of the layout of the national
economy should be combined with the optimization and upgrading of
industrial structure and the readjustment and improvement of the
structure of ownership, in a bid to enhance the state economy's
controlling power, the Decision says.
</P>
<P>
State economy enjoys a dominant stake in key industries and
crucial fields related to the lifeline of the national economy,
and in other industries and fields, the entire quality of state
economy could be improved through regrouping the assets and
readjusting the structure to centralize their capacity and
strengthening the key state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Various effective forms to realize public ownership should be
actively explored, and greater efforts be made to develop share-
holding economy and economies with mixed ownerships, while the
State controls the main stake in key enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The strategic regrouping of state-owned enterprises should be
continued in a bid to bring market mechanism into full play, and
efforts should be made to foster powerful and competitive larger
enterprises and enterprise groups and relax control over and
enliven small and mid-sized state-owned enterprises, the document
says.
</P>
<P>
To establish a modern enterprise system is the orientation of
the reform in state-owned enterprises and also an effective way to
combine public ownership and market economy.
</P>
<P>
The Decision points out that it is necessary to introduce
standardized corporate system reform into large and mid-sized
state-owned enterprises, and establish and improve the structure
of corporate legal person management, and be market-aware and
concentrate efforts on transforming enterprises' operating
mechanisms.
</P>
<P>
Improving the balance of assets and debts of the SOEs and
reducing their social burden should associate with preventing and
reducing financial risks, promoting internal restructuring and
fostering scientific management in SOEs.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
