<HEADLINE> 9 Killed, 38 Injured in Traffic Accident in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Nine people were killed and
38 others injured on Sunday in a traffic accident in southeastern
Turkey, the semi-official Anatolia news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred when a passenger bus turned over to the
shoulder of the Bingol-Mus highway near Seref village of Solhan
town in Bingol province.
</P>
<P>
The injured were rushed to Bingol State Hospital for medical
treatment, said the agency.
</P>
<P>
An investigation into the accident is underway. 
</P>
</TEXT>
