<HEADLINE> 7 Killed, 7 Wounded in Prison Riot in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Seven people were killed and
seven others injured in clashes between the Turkish security
forces and prisoners on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The incident happened when Turkish security forces tried to
enter into the wards in Ankara Center Jail early Sunday morning in
a bid to transfer the inmates to prisons in other provinces.
</P>
<P>
The prisoners set up barricades and used pistols or bottles to
stop the security forces from carrying out their mission, said
reliable sources, who asked not to be named.
</P>
<P>
Those injured have been sent to two hospitals in Ankara for
treatment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
