<HEADLINE> China Sets Trans-Century Blueprint for SOE Reform and Development ( 4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
These problems should be solved step by step through various
means in consideration of the country's current macro-economic and
financial situation to help enterprises increase flowing capital
and reduce debts.
</P>
<P>
Attention should be paid to keeping up with the global trend in
industrial restructuring and the changing demand of domestic and
overseas markets, and accelerate technological renovation and
elevation of industries.
</P>
<P>
With the market as a guide, advanced technology should be used
to transform traditional industries and strengthen technological
renovation in these industries with the goal of diversifying
products, improving quality, boosting efficiency, and spurring
exports.
</P>
<P>
The SOEs should hold an important position in new and hi-tech
industries and master core technologies so as to serve as
industrial leaders, the Decision notes.
</P>
<P>
The country must open wider to the outside world, establish a
sound legal system for the socialist market economy, develop
various markets, and maintain a stable economic order to create a
favorable macro-economic climate for the reform and development of
the SOEs.
</P>
<P>
Strengthening and improving the leadership of the Party is the
fundamental guarantee for speeding up the reform and development
of the SOEs, and it is imperative to bring into play the role of
the Party organizations as the political core in the SOEs, and
adhere to the principle of relying on the working class whole-
heartedly, the document stresses. 
</P>
