<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Modern Corporate System Key to China's SOE Reform (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 26 (Xinhua) -- To establish a modern
enterprise system is a necessary requirement to develop socialized
mass production and market economy and also an effective way to
combine public ownership and market economy, so it is the
orientation of the reform of China's state-owned enterprises,
according to a decision of the 15th Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC).
</P>
<P>
The Decision of the CPC Central Committee on Major Issues
Concerning the Reform and Development of State-Owned Enterprises,
which was made public today, notes that in the process of
establishing and improving the modern corporate system, efforts
should be made to fully understand and master requirements for a
clear definition of property rights, rights and duty, separation
of administrative and corporate functions, and scientific
management. And a good job is required in the following aspects:
</P>
<P>
-- Continue to push forward the task of separating
administrative and corporate functions.
</P>
<P>
The government performs the functions of stake holders in the
state-financed enterprises or state share-holding companies via
its designated representatives, enjoys rights to share assets
profits, makes major decisions and selects operation managers in
accordance with the scale of investment, and bears limited
responsibilities into enterprises' debts, but will not interfere
in daily operations of enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Party and government departments at different levels should
fully separate themselves from economic entities they run or
enterprises they directly administer in terms of personnel and
financial management.
</P>
<P>
-- Active efforts should be made to explore effective ways for
management of state assets.
</P>
<P>
It is necessary to gradually construct a network and mechanism
for management, supervision and operation of state assets in
accordance with the principles of the ownership by the state,
classified management, franchised operation and division of
supervision, and to establish and improve a strict responsibility
system.
</P>
<P>
Localities will be allowed and encouraged to make experiments
toward exploring the detailed measures for the management of state
assets.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990926.0088 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Modern Corporate System Key to China's SOE Reform (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
-- Introduce standardized corporate system reform into large
and medium-sized state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
It is necessary to clarify the duty of councils of share-
holders, the board of directors, the board of supervisors and
managerial ranks, form a corporate legal person management
structure by which each legal person is responsible for his own
duty and harmonious operation but is under effective restriction.
</P>
<P>
Diversity of equities is conducive to the formation of a
standardized corporate legal person management structure, and it
is necessary to make active efforts in developing companies
featuring multiple investing entities except a small number of
enterprises that should be monopolized by the state.
</P>
<P>
-- Be market-aware and concentrate efforts on transforming
enterprise operation mechanisms.
</P>
<P>
It is necessary to gradually establish mechanisms under which
successful enterprises survive and loss-incurring enterprises are
eliminated, operators can be promoted or demoted, personnel can be
employed or fired, income can be raised or be lowered,
technologies are kept upgrading, and the value of state assets are
preserved and incremented.
</P>
<P>
An income distribution system compatible with the modern
enterprise system should be established, and the practice of
members from the board of directors and the managerial ranks
obtaining rewards according to their respective duty and
contributions should be introduced under the guidance of the
policies of the state.
</P>
<P>
Salary standards of workers should be decided by enterprises in
accordance with the average social salary of different localities
and the performance of the enterprises. Inside the enterprises,
the principle of distribution according to work should be followed,
and proper income gaps will be allowed. Factors of production such
as capital and technologies will be permitted and encouraged to be
taken into account in distribution of profits.
</P>
<P>
Effective measures should be practiced to solve the current
problem that personal income of some monopolized industries are
too high.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
