<HEADLINE> Arab Diplomats Hail Mubarak for Accomplishments </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Senior Arab diplomats in Cairo
lauded on Sunday the efforts exerted by Egyptian President Hosni
Mubarak in helping realize regional peace and stability, and
improving the national economic landscape.
</P>
<P>
Arab League Assistant Secretary General Ahmed Bin Halay said
Mubarak "has a strategic vision" for peace and stability in the
Middle East and Egypt's drive to enhance economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Halay made the remarks in an interview with the Voice of Arab
radio on the occasion of Egypt's referendum which is certain to
endorse parliament nomination for Mubarak to stay in power for a
fourth six-year term.
</P>
<P>
"Mubarak has a clear strategic vision based on accurate
calculations and giving top priorities to the national dimension,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak was first elected president in 1981 after the
assassination of former president Anwar Sadat. He was re-elected
twice in 1987 and 1993.
</P>
<P>
During his 18 years in office, Mubarak has pushed forward the
peace process with Israel and kicked off a privatization program
making Egypt maintain one of the best economic performances in the
Middle East.
</P>
<P>
The parliament, the People's Assembly, nominated Mubarak for a
new term in July. Mubarak, who received 95 percent "yes" votes in
the past referendums, is set to win again this time.
</P>
<P>
In a separate interview with the Cairo-based radio, Algerian
Ambassador to Egypt Mostafa Sherif said Mubarak "has spared no
efforts to close the Arab ranks."
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian president "is respected and held in high esteem by
Algerians," Sherif said.
</P>
<P>
Lebanese Ambassador in Cairo Hisham Damashkia told the radio
that his country "fully supports Mubarak and hails his brave
stances on backing Arab causes." 
</P>
</TEXT>
