<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Sets Trans-Century Blueprint for SOE Reform and Development ( 1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 26 (Xinhua) -- The Decision of the Central
Committee of Communist Party of China (CPC) on Major Issues
Concerning the Reform and Development of State-owned Enterprises (
SOEs), adopted at the 4th Plenum of the 15th CPC Central Committee
on September 22, 1999, was officially issued here today.
</P>
<P>
The 15,000-word Decision, which consists of 12 parts, reaffirms
the leading role of state economy in the national economy and puts
forward trans-century objectives and guiding principles until 2010
for SOE reform and development.
</P>
<P>
The 4th Plenary Session of the 15th CPC Central Committee, held
in Beijing during September 19-22, stressed the SOEs' important
role in promoting the country's social and economic development as
well as in consolidating the socialist system.
</P>
<P>
The plenum pointed out that promoting SOE reform and
development is an important and pressing task. Currently, SOE
reform and development is at a critical stage, with some deep-
seated problems yet to be solved. And it is timely and necessary
for the session to concentrate on studying issues related to the
SOEs.
</P>
<P>
Since New China was founded 50 years ago and especially since
China's reform and opening-up, the Chinese people of all
nationalities have, through unremitting efforts, scored great
achievements in the socialist construction under the leadership of
the Party. China has developed from a poor and backward agrarian
country into a socialist country that will soon become well-off
and is striding toward the goal of industrialization and
modernization. This is a great historical leap forward in the
developing process of the Chinese nationality, to which SOEs and
the working class have made great and indelible contribution, the
Decision says.
</P>
</TEXT>
