<HEADLINE> Israel to Sell Missile Launchers to Venezuela </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Israel's Weapons Research
Institute, RAFAEL, will sell the Venezuelan air force three Barak
surface-to-surface missile launchers in a joint deal with a Dutch
company that supplies the control systems for the launchers,
Israel Radio reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Barak missile is vertically launched and is designed to
protect specific targets against any and all aerial threats,
including precision-guided and air-to-surface missiles.
</P>
<P>
The 2.2-meter-long missile is equipped with a warhead that
weighs 22 kilograms. It flies at twice the speed of sound and has
a range of about 12 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
The Venezuela army has also ordered an anti-aircraft
calibration system from RAFAEL with a contract worth of about 20
million U.S. dollars. 
</P>
