<HEADLINE> 500 Kenyans Die of AIDS Daily </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 26 (Xinhua) -- About 500 people die of AIDS
in Kenya every day, a senior Kenyan health official has revealed.
</P>
<P>
The Sunday Nation newspaper quoted Health Ministry Permanent
Secretary Julius Meme as saying that AIDS has become a major
public health concern and hindered economic development in Kenya.
</P>
<P>
"Seventy to 80 percent of those dying of the epidemic are aged
between 15 to 49 years, who are most economically productive, "
Meme said.
</P>
<P>
The productive capacity of these people have caused great
economic loss to the country, which amounts to over 200 million
shillings (about 2.7 million U.S. dollars) per day, said Meme.
</P>
<P>
"Out of the two million Kenyans infected with AIDS, 100,000 are
children below five years old," added Meme.
</P>
<P>
The Joint United Nations Program on AIDS estimates that by the
end of 1999, 33.4 million people will have been infected with HIV
in the world, and out of these 22 million are in sub-Sahara
Africa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
