<HEADLINE> Australia to Take on France in Davis Cup Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Australia will tackle France
in this year's Davis Cup tennis final after beating semi-final
rivals Russia in Brisbane on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Australians qualified for the December 3-5 final in either
Nice or Bordeaux after teenager Lleyton Hewitt thrashed world No.2
Yevgeny Kafelnikov in straight sets to give the home side an
unassailable 3-1 lead.
</P>
<P>
France made sure they would host the final after building an
unbeatable 3-0 lead over Belgium in Pau Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Australia holds a 9-3 record over the French in the Davis Cup
and beat them the last time they met 4-1 on grass at Sydney's
White City in 1997.
</P>
<P>
It will be Australia's 44th Davis Cup final and they will be
chasing their first win since 1986.
</P>
<P>
The last time the Australians reached the final was in 1993
when they lost 4-1 to Germany on clay in Dusseldorf in 1993.
</P>
<P>
Australia have won the Davis Cup 26 times, second only to the
United States' 31.
</P>
<P>
France will be playing in their 13th Davis Cup final, having
won it a total of eight times. Their last win was in 1996 against
Sweden in Malmo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
