<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore's Manufacturing Output Rises in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Singapore's manufacturing
output in August 1999 rose by 18.4 percent over a year earlier,
continuing a trend of two-digit growth for four months in a row,
Singapore Ministry of Trade and Industry said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
For the first eight months this year, manufacturing output grew
12.6 percent compared with the same period of last year, the
ministry said in a press release.
</P>
<P>
According to the ministry, all clusters in the manufacturing
sector recorded an increase in their August output with the
electronics cluster leading the gainers.
</P>
<P>
The electronics cluster gained 33.6 percent year-on-year in its
August output as strong demand for cellular phones and ICs boosted
output of telecommunication equipment and semiconductors
substantially.
</P>
<P>
The production of disk drives was slightly higher than a year
ago despite the restructuring by the drive makers but output of
PCBAs decreased due to less export demand.
</P>
<P>
The chemicals cluster grew by 16.7 percent over the same month
last year with the pharmaceuticals segment and the
industrial/specialty chemicals segment soaring by 54.3 percent and
63 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
However, output of petrochemicals and petroleum products in
August contracted by 3.3 and 19.4 percent year-on-year, offsetting
gains by the pharmaceuticals and the industrial/specialty
chemicals segment.
</P>
<P>
Output of the engineering cluster in August picked up 3.4
percent year-on-year as the 8.9-percent contraction in the
transport engineering segment dragged down a 14.1-percent hike in
the precision engineering segment and a marginal 1.8-percent
growth in the process engineering segment.
</P>
<P>
For the first eight months this year, the cumulative outputs of
the electronics and chemical clusters registered a 22.5- and
17.5-percent growth respectively while the engineering cluster
dipped 1.4 percent compared with the same period of last year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990926.0128 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-26 </DATE_TIME>
