<HEADLINE> Egyptian Parliament Leader Calls China Egypt's Sincere Friend </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Speaker of the Egyptian People'
s Assembly (Parliament) Ahmad Fathi Sorour said China is Egypt's
sincere friend that supports all just causes of the mankind.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua before the 50th anniversary of the
People's Republic of China, Sorour expressed confidence that the
cordial and historical friendship will last long between Egypt and
China.
</P>
<P>
Egypt took the lead in the Arab and African nations to set up
diplomatic ties with China in 1956, Sorour said, adding that this
step has yielded fruitful achievements through consistent
cooperation in bilateral relations and on regional and
international issues including the Middle East peace process and
human rights.
</P>
<P>
"I have visited China many times, and every time I find China
achieve new success in economic and social development," Sorour
said.
</P>
<P>
He praised the wise leadership of the Chinese government in
enabling the country to fall in line with the new international
economic environment without affecting its socialist system.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has also succeeded in forging a concord
between market liberalization and socialist market economy and in
forming strong economic and social structures, which have helped
China achieve rapid economic growth, he said.
</P>
<P>
Sorour praised China's foreign policy based on independence,
self reliance, opposition to hegemony and power politics, and
protection of world peace.
</P>
<P>
Over the past 50 years, China has made great achievements in
the diplomatic field, strengthening the traditional and cordial
relations with the Arab world and other developing countries, and
promoting ties with the developed countries including the United
States, Japan and the European Union members, he said.
</P>
<P>
China is now playing a more effective role in safeguarding
world peace, stability and development, the Egyptian parliament
leader noted.
</P>
<P>
The world community lauds China's prominent role in seeking
solutions to the Gulf crisis and the agreement on Cambodia as well
as in enhancing dialogue aimed at securing peace on the Korean
peninsular, controlling armament and building of a new world order,
Sorour said.
</P>
<P>
Sorour said it is a must that economic relations be developed
and boosted between Egypt and China to reach the same lofty level
as political relations. And to benefit from the great potentials
of the Chinese market, Egypt can increase its exports and expand
the scope of trade exchanges between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Sorour said he hoped that China would play a more effective
role in regional and international politics in the coming century,
shouldering more responsibilities and tasks in protecting the
rights and interests of the developing countries as well as the
world peace and stability. 
</P>
</TEXT>
