<HEADLINE> Nicaragua Declares Sanitary Alert Against Epidemic Outbreak </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Nicaraguan Health Ministry
authorities Saturday declared a sanitary alert against possible
outbreak of meningitis or leptospirosis in the Rivas department in
the south of the country.
</P>
<P>
Four persons with meningococcical meningitis symptoms have died
since August, said Julio Flores, the ministry's delegate in the
region, who did not rule out the possibility of leptospirosis
eruption.
</P>
<P>
Two of the victims were minors, aged eight and 10 respectively.
Their symptoms were vomiting, dizziness, rigidity in the back of
the neck and low blood pressure, which are symptoms of meningitis,
a disease caused either by microbes or viruses, said Flores.
</P>
<P>
The first fatal case, a 46-year-old man, happened in August,
and the others were registered this month, but the causes have not
yet been completely determined.
</P>
<P>
Leptospirosis, caused by spirochetes and characterized by fever,
hepatitis with jaundice and hemorrhages, is usually spread by rat
infestation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
