<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South Korean President Hails China's Achievements in Past 50 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, September 26 (Xinhua) -- South Korean President Kim Dae-
jung conveyed his hearty congratulations on the 50th anniversary
of the People's Republic of China and highly praised China's great
achievements in the past 50 years.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua, Kim said that during these years,
China has made "very impressive" development. Especially in the 20
years or so of reform and opening-up, China's economy has
witnessed "a surprisingly high growth of 9.8 percent per year."
Internationally, it has also "ensured the position as a great
nation in politics and economy."
</P>
<P>
Recalling his four visits to China, Kim said he has noticed the
resolution of the Chinese leaders and people in carrying forward
the reform and opening-up policy and is sure that China will make
greater progress in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
He extended his hearty respects to Chinese leaders Deng
Xiaoping and Jiang Zemin who have led the nation to prosperity and
to the Chinese people who have made great efforts under their
leadership.
</P>
<P>
Talking about China's role in Asia and the world, Kim Dae-jung
noted that China is "one of the most influential countries" not
only in Northeast Asia and Asia, but also in the world by making
significant contributions to peace, security and prosperity.
</P>
<P>
In Northeast Asia, he said, China has played an active part in
the four-party talks on the Korean Peninsula issue, whose purpose
is to secure peace. In Asia, China has played an active role in
the Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation forum and the ASEAN Regional
Forum, and has contributed to regional peace and prosperity
through regional cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Kim Dae-jung said the reason why China is so important in the
international society lies in "the success of its reform and
opening-up policy and the independent foreign policy of peace it
has been pursuing in the last 20 years." He said he was sure that
China will make greater progress and contribution to regional and
global peace and prosperity.
</P>
<P>
He said that "China has a very bright future" and "will make
greater achievements" because the country has "the eminent
leadership of Jiang Zemin and his colleagues, the excellence of
the Chinese people and the infinite potentiality of its national
economy."
</P>
<P>
Kim Dae-jung said that South Korea "cares for and anticipates"
the improvement of its relationship with China, as it is "not only
vital for their common prosperity, but also for peace and security
in East Asia." He said he was "very satisfied" that bilateral
relationship has moved forward significantly since his visit to
China last November to sign the agreement with President Jiang
Zemin on the establishment of a "cooperative partnership" oriented
toward the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
He said that China is "the most indispensable, the most
important and the most valuable neighbor" of South Korea and that
it is "absolutely essential" that the close cooperation between
South Korea and China continues to contribute to peace in the
Korean Peninsula and East Asia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
