<HEADLINE> Chinese Art Troupe Performs in Islamabad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 25 (Xinhua) -- China's Gansu Acrobatic
Troupe gave a thrilling performance here Saturday night at the Lok
Virsa open air theater before an audience of more than 3,000.
</P>
<P>
The programs performed Saturday night included "handstand on
pipa," "hand juggling," "feet juggling" and "jar trick" which were
full of the rich flavor of Chinese culture and modern life.
</P>
<P>
Pakistani Information Minister Mushahid Hussain, Director
General of the National Council of the Arts Ghulam Rasul and
Chinese Ambassador to Pakistan Lu ShuLin watched the performance
which lasted for about two hours.
</P>
<P>
The Gansu Acrobatic Troupe was founded in 1960 and has visited
more than 20 countries and regions. However, this is its first
visit to South Asia.
</P>
<P>
The troupe arrived in Pakistan's southern port city of Karachi
on September 16 at the invitation of Pakistan's Ministry for
Information and Culture.
</P>
<P>
They are here to participate in various activities launched by
the Pakistani government to celebrate the 50th anniversary of the
founding of the People's Republic China.
</P>
<P>
The troupe has already performed in Karachi and Quetta and will
also perform in Pakistan's other major cities before their
departure on October 6. 
