<HEADLINE> German Ullrich on Brink of Tour of Spain Victory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Germany's Jan Ullrich was
ready to secure his second major Tour title after his 1997 Tour de
France triumph following an outstanding ride to win the 20th and
penultimate stage of the Tour of Spain on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Ullrich sped through the 46.5 kms time trial between El Tiemblo
and Avila in one hour four minutes and 57 seconds to extend his
race lead to an almost impregnable four minutes 15 seconds over
Spain's Igor Gonzalez Galdeano.
</P>
<P>
The Deutsche Telekom rider came home two minutes 50 seconds
ahead of the next fastest, Switzerland's Alex Zuelle, for his
second stage victory of the Tour.
</P>
<P>
Sunday's final stage into Madrid, which concludes with eight
laps around the Spanish capital, is expected to be a victory
parade for Ullrich. 
</P>
