<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Loses Doubles Davis Cup Match </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's tennis team failed
to seal the Davis Cup Group qualifying tie at the Harare City
Sports Centre on Saturday losing 6-3, 2-6, 6-4, 2-6 and 4-6 in
doubles match against Chile.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe's doubles duo of Byron and Wayne Black failed to
content with the powerful shorts from Chaileans Nicolas Mass and
Fernando Gonzalez, leaving the contest for a place in the Davis
Cup finals open.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe had got to a good start on Friday when number two
Wayne upset former world number one and Chilean number one Marcel
Rios in the single matches after his brother Byron had dismissed
Mass in the first game of the singles matches.
</P>
<P>
The Chilean display in the doubles matches meant that Zimbabwe
have to win one of the reverse singles on Sunday to qualify.
</P>
<P>
The reserve singles would see Zimbabwe number one Byron
battling it out against Chilean number one Rios. Wayne would take
on Chilean number two Mass. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
