<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Man United Held 3-3 at English Premier League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 25 (Xinhua) -- English premier league leaders
Manchester United were held three-all by visitors Southampton on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The result cut their lead in the league from four points to two.
</P>
<P>
Dwight Yorke scored twice for the Reds but he was matched by
Southampton substitute Matt Le Tissier, whose first goal to level
at 2-2 dribbled through goalkeeper Massimo Taibi's legs.
</P>
<P>
Leeds United edged closer to the leaders after an equally-
thrilling home encounter with Newcastle, finally sealing a 3-2 win
through Michael Bridges's 77th-minute goal. Alan Shearer scored
both Newcastle's goals.
</P>
<P>
Manchester United now have 21 points while Leeds have 19, also
from nine games.
</P>
<P>
Arsenal, in third, also have 19 after snatching a 1-0 home win
over Watford, Nwankwo Kanu scoring with two minutes to go.
</P>
<P>
Surprise success story Sunderland went fourth, on 17, with a 1-
0 victory over bottom club Sheffield Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
