<HEADLINE> U.S. Driver Dies in Race Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 25 (Xinhua) -- American driver Kevin
Gobrecht died Saturday after an accident during a World of Outlaws
preliminary race in Greenwood, Nebraska, the United States.
</P>
<P>
Gobrecht's car was hit by a car driven by Matt Moro, who was
not injured, during a turn at NAPA I-80 Speedway on Friday night.
</P>
<P>
He was brought to a medical center where he died shortly after
midnight, hospital administrator Jim Nisley said.
</P>
<P>
Gobrecht, 30, was in his first season on the World of Outlaws
circuit, spokesman Richard Day said. 
</P>
