<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT, September 26 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- Belarus said Saturday that it would introduce
a draft resolution at the 54th session of the United Nations
General Assembly aimed at barring development and manufacture of
new weapons of mass destruction.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the general debate of the current session of the
General Assembly, Ural Latypov, minister of foreign affairs of
Belarus, said his country made an historic decision a few years
ago when it relinquished possession of nuclear arms inherited from
the former Soviet Union. (UN-Belarus-Statement)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PANAMA CITY -- Panama and the United States have signed a
letter of understanding to improve their cooperation in the anti-
drug war.
</P>
<P>
The letter of understanding was signed Friday by Panamanian
Interior and Justice Minister Winston Spadafora and U.S.
ambassador to Panama Simon Ferro, said local press reports
Saturday. (Panama-US)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
QUITO -- Ecuadorian President Jamil Mahuad on Saturday asked
the international financing organizations to reduce the burden of
the Ecuadorian foreign debt because of the economic incapacity of
the country.
</P>
<P>
Ecuador cannot pay the present debt of 16 billion U.S. dollars,
said Mahuad in his Saturday speech broadcast to the nation. (
Ecuador-Foreign Debt)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BONN -- German Chancellor Gerhard Schroeder and French Premier
Lionel Jospin underlined here Saturday the importance of the
European Union's rapid enlargement toward the east.
</P>
<P>
Meeting at the eastern German town of Genshagen near Berlin,
the two leaders stressed the necessity to draw in all European
people as the direct consequence of the Kosovo war. (Germany-
France-Visit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- Without enhancing the authority of the
General Assembly and without early restructuring of the Security
Council, the United Nations would be unable to meet the demands of
a rapidly changing situation and cope with new challenges, the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) said here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the general debate of the 54th session of the
General Assembly, DPRK Minister for Foreign Affairs Paek Nam Sun
said the authority of the General Assembly where all member states
are represented and interact democratically on an equal footing
should be enhanced. (UN-DPRK-Statement)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LIMA -- U.S. ambassador in Bolivia Donna Hrinak denied that her
country plans to install a military base in that country, but
revealed that it is negotiating the permanence of its aircraft in
several strategic points of South America.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here from Santa Cruz, Bolivia, quoted Hrinak
as saying that U.S. military presence in Bolivia was for
performing social work, and they will leave next week. (Bolivia-
Military Base) 
</P>
